---
// UpgradeProblem — short, punchy problem statement.
// Voice rule: no "solutions," no overclaim language. "We close the gap."
---
<!-- PROBLEM SECTION -->
<section id="problem" class="relative border-b border-line bg-surface-1/40">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-20 sm:py-24">
    <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> The Gap</span>
    <h2 class="mt-5 text-[2rem] sm:text-[2.6rem] leading-[1.05] font-bold">
      Your shop feels premium. <span class="text-accent">Your Square page feels basic.</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-7 space-y-5 text-[1.05rem] sm:text-[1.12rem] leading-relaxed text-text-soft max-w-2xl">
      <p>
        You've built the chairs, the vibe, the reviews, the staff, the reputation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then a new customer taps your website and lands on a generic booking page that looks like every other shop using Square.
      </p>
      <p>
        The booking works. The experience doesn't sell the brand.
      </p>
      <p>
        And when customers are comparing three shops on their phone, that gap matters.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text font-medium text-[1.15rem]">
        We close the gap.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- /PROBLEM SECTION -->
